import { Link, useLocation, useHistory } from 'react-router-dom' import { useEffect, useState } from 'react' import pokemonproject from '../Assets/pokemonproject.png' export default function PokemonDetails() { const location = useLocation() const number = location.state.number const source = `https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/${number}.png` const [pokemon, setPokemon] = useState({}) console.log(number, ' number') useEffect(() => { fetch(`https://pokeapi.co/api/v2/pokemon/${number}/`) .then((response) => response.json()) .then((data) => { console.log(data, 'pokemon') setPokemon(data) document.getElementById('Sprite').src = source document.getElementById('Fill1').style = { width: data.stats[0].base_stat, } }) .catch((err) => { console.log('Error encountered') }) }, []) const toInitialMayusc = (str) => str.charAt(0).toUpperCase() + str.slice(1) return (

Type:{' '} {pokemon?.types?.length ? toInitialMayusc(pokemon?.types[0]?.type.name) : 'Loading...'} {pokemon?.types?.length ? ' & ' + toInitialMayusc(pokemon?.types[1]?.type.name) : 'Loading...'}

Number: {number}
Name: {pokemon.name}
Height: {pokemon.height}
Weight: {pokemon.weight}
Stats:

Hp:{' '} {pokemon?.stats?.length ? pokemon?.stats[0]?.base_stat : 'Loading...'}

Special Attack:{' '} {pokemon?.stats?.length ? pokemon?.stats[3]?.base_stat : 'Loading...'}

Special Defense:{' '} {pokemon?.stats?.length ? pokemon?.stats[4]?.base_stat : 'Loading...'}
